  "full_text": "Gastropod\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n2\nSystems\nHooked Proboscis\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nGrapple for 1 damage, pulling the Vek towards objects or units to the Vek.\nThe\nGastropod\nis a common\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\nintroduced in the Advanced Edition. They are only present if Advanced Enemies are turned on at the start of a new timeline.\nDescription\n[\n]\nGastropods fire a grappling hook that deals 1 damage to the target and either pulls it to the Gastropod or the other way around, depending on if the target is immovable. If the hook does not hit anything the Gastropod does not move. Despite being based off an aquatic animal they are able to drown.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nMuch like the\nFirefly\n, the Gastropod's high health and projectile-based attack are very dangerous in the early game since they are difficult to remove. However, Gastropods can pull other Vek away from targets and lack non-grappling movement, which can be used to your advantage in protecting objectives or the grid.\nGastropods are also capable of pulling themselves towards solid structures, including\nMountains\n. In particular, try and redirect their attack so that they pull themselves to a mountain located right next to a chasm or water tile, and they'll instantly be destroyed after attacking.\nv\n\u00b7\nd\n\u00b7\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n\u2022\nBlobber\n\u2022\nBurrower\n\u2022\nCentipede\n\u2022\nCrab\n\u2022\nDigger\n\u2022\nFirefly\n\u2022\nHornet\n\u2022\nLeaper\n\u2022\nScarab\n\u2022\nScorpion\n\u2022\nSpider\n\u2022\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n\u2022\nGastropod\n\u2022\nMosquito\n\u2022\nMoth\n\u2022\nPlasmodia\n\u2022\nStarfish\n\u2022\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n\u2022\nAlpha Blobber\n\u2022\nAlpha Burrower\n\u2022\nAlpha Centipede\n\u2022\nAlpha Crab\n\u2022\nAlpha Digger\n\u2022\nAlpha Firefly\n\u2022\nAlpha Hornet\n\u2022\nAlpha Leaper\n\u2022\nAlpha Scarab\n\u2022\nAlpha Scorpion\n\u2022\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n\u2022\nAlpha Gastropod\n\u2022\nAlpha Mosquito\n\u2022\nAlpha Moth\n\u2022\nAlpha Plasmodia\n\u2022\nAlpha Starfish\n\u2022\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n\u2022\nBlood Psion\n\u2022\nShell Psion\n\u2022\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n\u2022\nRaging Psion\n\u2022\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n\u2022\nAlpha Blob\n\u2022\nSpiderling Egg\n\u2022\nSpiderling\n\u2022\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n\u2022\nAlpha Spore\n\u2022\nVicious Spore\n\u2022\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n\u2022\nFirefly Leader\n\u2022\nHornet Leader\n\u2022\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) \u2022\nPsion Abomination\n\u2022\nScorpion Leader\n\u2022\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n\u2022\nBouncer Leader\n\u2022\nCentipede Leader\n\u2022\nCrab Leader\n\u2022\nGastropod Leader\n\u2022\nMosquito Leader\n\u2022\nPlasmodia Leader\n\u2022\nScarab Leader\n\u2022\nStarfish Leader\n\u2022\nTumblebug Leader",
